The Telegraph - Calcutta
 BCCI, govt praise PCB
Islamabad: Indian sports minister Vikram Verma and BCCI president Jaghmohan Dalmiya have showered lavish praise on the Pakistan government, its cricket board and the people for their exemplary hospitality. Let me thank you for the courtesies extended to my colleagues and me during our memorable visit to Lahore, Verma said in a letter to Shaharyar Khan. Dalmiya, in his letter to Rameez Raja, said the BCCI was delighted the Indian teams tour of Pakistan after a gap of 14 years went so successfully. (PTI)  Copyright 
